00:32:53,450 --> 00:32:56,949
Scott: Because, I mean, you could just surround the castle and nothing else, but then you wouldn't have any area.

631
00:32:57,110 --> 00:33:01,370
Scott: You've also got to surround land, you know, so that you have areas to put your cannons.

632
00:33:01,810 --> 00:33:02,716
Rym: Also getting points.

633
00:33:02,817 --> 00:33:04,870
Rym: More points means more cannons and it means winning.

634
00:33:05,712 --> 00:33:11,810
Scott: So ideally, the ideal play would be to completely surround your entire area with one layer of walls.

635
00:33:12,252 --> 00:33:15,070
Scott: And the entire inner area would be just completely open.

636
00:33:15,130 --> 00:33:16,485
Scott: And that is never even close to happening.

637
00:33:17,551 --> 00:33:18,890
Rym: You've got like 20 fucking seconds.

638
00:33:18,990 --> 00:33:20,270
Scott: If you do that, you're fucking cheating.

639
00:33:22,735 --> 00:33:24,285
Scott: And you get your first castle for free.

640
00:33:24,466 --> 00:33:25,070
Scott: It's not too bad.

641
00:33:25,676 --> 00:33:26,970
Scott: So then you get to place cannons.

642
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:30,410
Scott: And the more area you've got surrounded, the more cannons you get to place.

643
00:33:30,670 --> 00:33:35,310
Scott: But, if you place too many cannons, it's hard to surround the cannons, you see.

644
00:33:35,730 --> 00:33:37,630
Scott: Because you can't put pieces where the cannons are.

645
00:33:37,650 --> 00:33:39,089
Rym: You also can't get rid of cannons.

646
00:33:39,832 --> 00:33:41,170
Scott: Oh, you can if someone helps you out.

647
00:33:41,170 --> 00:33:42,190
Rym: No, they stay there broken.

648
00:33:42,231 --> 00:33:43,386
Scott: They stay there broken, so.

649
00:33:44,111 --> 00:33:45,270
Rym: Because here's the deal with this game.

650
00:33:45,390 --> 00:33:46,478
Rym: Alright, it sounds pretty simple.

651
00:33:46,518 --> 00:33:48,150
Rym: I shoot the other guy's walls, then we build.

652
00:33:48,630 --> 00:33:53,970
Rym: So, smart people will shoot like one hole in the corner surrounded by other blocks.

653
00:33:54,251 --> 00:33:57,930
Rym: So the dude literally needs a one piece or he cannot survive.

654
00:33:58,370 --> 00:34:02,230
Scott: Yup, and basically if he doesn't get a one piece, he's gotta use all his pieces to surround some other castle.

655
00:34:02,410 --> 00:34:04,630
Scott: Because that first castle, it ain't gonna happen this turn.

656
00:34:04,630 --> 00:34:08,268
Rym: Many times, I'll have one awesome castle with like nine cannons in it.

657
00:34:08,590 --> 00:34:09,489
Rym: That is just fucked.

658
00:34:09,810 --> 00:34:14,429
Rym: And I'm holding on to like another castle on the other side of my territory with like one baby cannon in there.

659
00:34:14,630 --> 00:34:17,030
Scott: Waiting for a one piece to save the previous castle.

660
00:34:17,270 --> 00:34:22,409
Scott: And of course, every turn, the big swipe comes down and wipes away a whole bunch of pieces.

661
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:26,590
Rym: Every round that you have one cannon and Rym's playing, Rym's blowing up that cannon.

662
00:34:26,870 --> 00:34:29,489
Scott: That's right, because you can destroy someone else's cannon with ten bullets.

663
00:34:30,030 --> 00:34:32,810
Scott: So if you fire ten bullets, you can destroy someone else's cannon.

664
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:34,789
Scott: If they only have one, now they can't shoot at you this turn.

665
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:35,989
Scott: I cannot express to you.

666
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:38,969
Scott: Maybe they'll get one shot off because the shooting is real time.

667
00:34:39,350 --> 00:34:41,690
Scott: Maybe they'll get one or two shots off before you destroy their cannon.

668
00:34:41,730 --> 00:34:44,770
Rym: How crazy fun Rampart is in direct versus.

669
00:34:45,071 --> 00:34:46,409
Scott: Rampart is the most fun.

670
00:34:46,550 --> 00:34:52,070
Rym: It has this right balance of multiple game modes, very quick gameplay, very high skill cap.

671
00:34:52,170 --> 00:34:54,085
Rym: Like your skill matters a lot.

672
00:34:54,730 --> 00:34:55,188
Scott: A whole lot.

673
00:34:55,451 --> 00:34:57,270
Rym: And it's one of those games, kind of like a fighting game.

674
00:34:57,470 --> 00:35:01,649
Rym: Where, you know, if I play against a random M. Bison online, I don't even get a hit in.

675
00:35:02,031 --> 00:35:03,409
Rym: Like it's like start and I'm dead.

676
00:35:04,011 --> 00:35:06,990
Rym: That's the way a noob is against someone who's played Rampart in Rampart.

677
00:35:07,050 --> 00:35:10,530
Scott: Yeah, you're not going to surround your castle and therefore you're not going to stay alive.

678
00:35:11,130 --> 00:35:13,730
Scott: The worst, the thing about Rampart is the way the game works, right?

679
00:35:13,870 --> 00:35:17,650
Scott: Is if you die three times, you lose because you get three continues.

680
00:35:17,950 --> 00:35:19,830
Rym: Well, no, that's just because we're playing the Maim ROM.

681
00:35:19,990 --> 00:35:21,090
Rym: I mean, you decide the rules.

682
00:35:21,150 --> 00:35:22,058
Rym: You can mess with that.

683
00:35:22,098 --> 00:35:23,510
Rym: You can say no continues, whatever.

684
00:35:23,890 --> 00:35:30,630
Scott: But anyway, if you, if everyone dies in the same time, then whoever's the highest score actually wins.

685
00:35:30,690 --> 00:35:35,890
Scott: And if everyone survives to the final battle, then whoever's the highest score wins.

686
00:35:36,411 --> 00:35:42,829
Scott: But no matter how many continues you have, if you die or how much higher your score is, if you die on the final battle, that's it.

687
00:35:43,451 --> 00:35:44,830
Rym: So sometimes you got to go for it.

688
00:35:44,850 --> 00:35:51,095
Rym: You're like, all right, I'm going to die on purpose now to try to get more points by starting fresh and getting rid of all this BS.

689
00:35:51,477 --> 00:35:54,810
Rym: But maybe now I'll die for real because I run out of lives.

690
00:35:54,870 --> 00:35:57,302
Scott: Yeah, or like one, let's say one guy's doing so well.

691
00:35:57,343 --> 00:35:58,810
Scott: He's got all his castles surrounded.

692
00:35:58,970 --> 00:36:02,069
Scott: He's got a ton of cannons and every single round he's getting a zillion points.

693
00:36:02,750 --> 00:36:14,515
Scott: But if you find a way to just be alive for the final battle and then poke him in just the right spot to where he cannot survive on the final battle, even though he's got a bajillion points and you survive, you could win that.

694
00:36:14,938 --> 00:36:16,690
Scott: So you don't give up until the very end.

695
00:36:16,810 --> 00:36:19,750
Rym: So it's the game that has a very good mechanic of you're never out.

696
00:36:19,950 --> 00:36:28,850
Scott: You can always still if you're alive, if you're alive and you surround the castle and you surround it, if you have at least one castle surrounded, you can win Rampart.

697
00:36:29,371 --> 00:36:32,590
Rym: Now, one reason we bring this game up, I mean, there's not that much else to say about it.

698
00:36:32,811 --> 00:36:36,970
Rym: The SNES like that port of it actually has a lot more going on.

699
00:36:37,190 --> 00:36:41,010
Scott: The only versions of Rampart I've ever seen are the SNES version, which is different.

700
00:36:41,211 --> 00:36:47,930
Scott: I think the arcade version, which is the same as the one that's in Midway Arcade Classics, because it's just a main ROM of the arcade version.

701
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:56,469
Rym: The SNES one, you can build a mega cannon that shoots way slow and takes a bunch of normal cannons up, but it leaves fire that you can't build stuff on.

702
00:36:56,750 --> 00:37:00,630
Scott: There's also a single player Rampart where there's boats and soldiers attacking you.

703
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:02,029
Rym: Yeah, the boats drop tanks, grunts.

704
00:37:02,430 --> 00:37:03,844
Scott: Yeah, but it's kind of bleh.

705
00:37:03,865 --> 00:37:04,329
Scott: I don't like it.

706
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:05,373
Rym: Well, it would be fun.

707
00:37:06,196 --> 00:37:10,090
Rym: My biggest complaint with Rampart is that for its time, it is unparalleled.

708
00:37:10,351 --> 00:37:11,674
Rym: It is an amazing game.

709
00:37:12,195 --> 00:37:17,268
Rym: And yet, to this day, no one has made that game again.

710
00:37:17,288 --> 00:37:17,368
Rym: well.

711
00:37:19,252 --> 00:37:23,250
Rym: It's one of those games, like, you know, we did this panel at PAX, egregiously unrealized potential.

712
00:37:23,730 --> 00:37:25,156
Rym: And we didn't talk about Rampart.

713
00:37:25,217 --> 00:37:28,250
Rym: Rampart is one of the most painfully unrealized.

714
00:37:28,591 --> 00:37:32,270
Rym: Anyone could just take this game and make the same goddamn game.

715
00:37:32,290 --> 00:37:37,950
Scott: With no changes, just add network multiplayer and control it with the mouse, and it would be awesome.

716
00:37:39,493 --> 00:37:40,624
Scott: No changes, no thought.

717
00:37:40,644 --> 00:37:41,250
Scott: You just clone it.

718
00:37:41,370 --> 00:37:44,246
Rym: Or go one step further and make it, like, crazy.

719
00:37:44,306 --> 00:37:44,970
Rym: Like, add stuff.

720
00:37:45,351 --> 00:37:48,370
Scott: Yeah, I'm saying it would be awesome if you did nothing.

721
00:37:48,951 --> 00:37:52,090
Scott: But assuming you're going to do something, you can only make it more awesome, right?

722
00:37:52,330 --> 00:37:54,909
Scott: Here's some things that can make Rampart even more awesome, right?

723
00:37:55,972 --> 00:37:57,709
Scott: Co-op versus the computer mode.

724
00:37:58,010 --> 00:37:59,709
Scott: Co-op, like, teams versus teams.

725
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:01,058
Scott: Four player mode.

726
00:38:01,078 --> 00:38:01,964
Scott: Two on two mode.

727
00:38:03,030 --> 00:38:03,788
Rym: Eight players.

728
00:38:04,894 --> 00:38:09,510
Scott: You know, varying numbers of continues, changing rule sets, different stuff like that.

729
00:38:09,690 --> 00:38:17,926
Scott: Maybe a mode where you can place a cannon, but if you place a cannon outside your walls or in the water, it makes a boat that attacks the other guys instead of a cannon, right?

730
00:38:17,946 --> 00:38:18,590
Scott: You have options.

731
00:38:19,090 --> 00:38:23,330
Rym: Or maybe you've also got the armies, you know, the little grunts, and you're standing after each other.

732
00:38:23,390 --> 00:38:29,770
Scott: You could choose cannons, make a fast cannon or a slow, powerful cannon where the cannonball destroys four squares.

733
00:38:30,393 --> 00:38:33,310
Scott: Or destroys a cannon in two hits, or, you know, stuff like that.

734
00:38:33,790 --> 00:38:35,389
Scott: You know, you can mix it up a little bit in there.

735
00:38:35,910 --> 00:38:38,170
Rym: I mean, or go one step further, like, my crazy idea.

736
00:38:38,691 --> 00:38:40,809
Rym: I don't think I have the resources to make this.

737
00:38:41,210 --> 00:38:44,630
Rym: You know, Guns of Icarus, Muse, they made that, Emily and Alex and all our friends.

738
00:38:45,091 --> 00:38:50,190
Rym: But it was the idea that it was a co-op FPS tower defense kind of game, you know, on an airship.

739
00:38:50,731 --> 00:38:58,370
Rym: What if Rampart was an NS style, you're running around in effectively Minecraft building walls and manning cannons.

740
00:38:58,490 --> 00:38:59,676
Scott: Well that was an idea I had, right?

741
00:38:59,717 --> 00:39:01,747
Scott: What if you just took Minecraft and the way it worked is?

742
00:39:01,767 --> 00:39:02,350
Scott: there were cannons.

743
00:39:02,990 --> 00:39:04,721
Scott: And there were two sides and there was water.

744
00:39:04,741 --> 00:39:06,049
Scott: you couldn't cross between them.

745
00:39:06,830 --> 00:39:09,790
Scott: And the game, everyone had a castle that they had to defend.

746
00:39:10,230 --> 00:39:12,490
Scott: So basically it would be like, alright, the timer begins, go.

747
00:39:12,630 --> 00:39:14,710
Scott: And everyone has to build walls in Minecraft.

748
00:39:14,930 --> 00:39:20,930
Scott: So you have a whole team of people, tons of people building walls in between the enemy and your castle.

749
00:39:21,450 --> 00:39:22,787
Scott: And then you'd be like, alright, time's up.

750
00:39:23,491 --> 00:39:31,530
Scott: Now everyone fire cannons and you aim, everyone plays an FPS where they stand still and shoot cannons at the enemy's walls trying to hit the enemy's castle.

751
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:35,510
Scott: And then time's up, rebuild walls and you keep switching back and forth.

752
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:40,670
Rym: There are nearly infinite variations on this theme and all of them, it's kind of like when we were talking about...

753
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:42,590
Scott: It'd be hard to make a version that was not good.

754
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:45,862
Rym: It's kind of like when we were talking about Fallout 3 and how it was fun.

755
00:39:46,203 --> 00:39:53,630
Rym: but if they just removed all that combat BS and just made it a series of really interesting, basically a graphical choose your own adventure with a lot of stuff.

756
00:39:54,211 --> 00:39:55,800
Rym: We dismissed it like, yeah, that's just a big.

757
00:39:55,820 --> 00:39:57,308
Rym: choose your own adventure, dot dot dot.

758
00:39:57,811 --> 00:39:59,849
Rym: And I would play the ever living fuck out of a game like that.

759
00:40:00,050 --> 00:40:05,430
Scott: Yeah, if it was just the choose your own adventure and didn't try to cloud it with stupid RPG leveling and combat.

760
00:40:05,470 --> 00:40:07,279
Rym: I'd play the crap out of old Rampart.

761
00:40:07,359 --> 00:40:08,023
Rym: A new Rampart?

762
00:40:08,204 --> 00:40:09,490
Rym: I would play that every day.

763
00:40:09,510 --> 00:40:11,137
Scott: Yeah, we still play old Rampart.

764
00:40:11,177 --> 00:40:12,161
Scott: It's sort of like Bomberman.

765
00:40:12,181 --> 00:40:14,370
Scott: You whip it out at the parties and it's always a hit.

766
00:40:15,771 --> 00:40:21,550
Scott: And the thing is, unlike Bomberman where you have to worry about what version to play, you can't go wrong because there's only one version of Rampart.

767
00:40:22,070 --> 00:40:23,090
Rym: Well, there's the SNES one.

768
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:25,090
Scott: But that's only two player max, it's no good.

769
00:40:26,314 --> 00:40:28,329
Scott: You can't get the four score in on that, it doesn't work.

770
00:40:29,251 --> 00:40:31,017
Rym: Yeah, but three player works well.

771
00:40:31,057 --> 00:40:35,110
Rym: but it also has that kind of game theory problem that all three player games have.

772
00:40:35,310 --> 00:40:38,630
Rym: Which is, Scott always claims that everyone just attacked him and that's why he died.

773
00:40:38,790 --> 00:40:39,810
Scott: Which is true, sometimes.

774
00:40:39,850 --> 00:40:40,050
Scott: Never.

775
00:40:40,272 --> 00:40:40,750
Scott: It's possible.

776
00:40:41,234 --> 00:40:41,970
Rym: It is possible.

777
00:40:42,092 --> 00:40:42,528
Scott: And it happens.

778
00:40:44,152 --> 00:40:48,450
Scott: Usually what happens in Rampart is whoever looks like they're doing well is going to get ganged up on.

779
00:40:48,710 --> 00:40:54,530
Scott: If someone has a whole bunch of walls and a whole bunch of cannons, then the other two players are going to concentrate their fire on that guy first.

780
00:40:54,910 --> 00:40:56,510
Scott: And then maybe shoot each other a little bit.

781
00:40:56,630 --> 00:40:58,249
Rym: It's always funny to watch us play.

782
00:40:58,531 --> 00:41:03,650
Scott: And then the guy who's doing really well is going to concentrate most of his fire on the guy who's doing second best.

783
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:07,130
Scott: And then maybe fire some token shots at the guy who's doing third best.

784
00:41:07,631 --> 00:41:13,970
Rym: But every time we're playing, you'll see right before the game starts, Scott and I both have our crosshairs over Scott Johnson.

785
00:41:14,530 --> 00:41:18,550
Rym: And then as soon as firing starts, suddenly my crosshairs go to Scott, who's going to me?

786
00:41:19,472 --> 00:41:24,630
Scott: The thing is, in Rampart, let's say someone is doing kind of shitty but they're alive.

787
00:41:25,333 --> 00:41:26,309
Scott: They've got one cannon.

788
00:41:27,130 --> 00:41:34,310
Scott: If you ignore that guy who's in last place for even one round, you don't fire a single shot at him, the next round he's going to be insanely powerful.

789
00:41:34,370 --> 00:41:38,090
Scott: He's going to surround a second castle and fill it in with six cannons and have seven cannons.

790
00:41:38,571 --> 00:41:42,870
Scott: So even though a guy's in third place, you cannot afford to completely ignore him.

791
00:41:42,950 --> 00:41:47,229
Scott: You've got to fire some bullets his way to force him to do some work every round.

792
00:41:48,032 --> 00:41:49,350
Scott: Otherwise you're asking for it.

793
00:41:49,470 --> 00:41:58,590
Rym: The game multiplayer-wise also has the good continuing mechanic of as you keep playing games, the scores continue to recrue and whoever won the last round gets increasingly handicapped.

794
00:41:58,770 --> 00:42:05,970
Scott: Yeah, if you play multiple rounds of Rampart, so we play a round and we go all the way to final battle and Rym wins.

795
00:42:06,570 --> 00:42:07,615
Scott: Then we play another round.

796
00:42:07,896 --> 00:42:10,750
Scott: Rym only has three castles and everyone else has four castles.

797
00:42:10,890 --> 00:42:15,290
Scott: It actually gives Rym a disadvantage because he won the prior rounds.

798
00:42:17,312 --> 00:42:22,750
Scott: Also, I'm not completely sure about this, but when you're on your second and third continues, your cannons look different?

799
00:42:22,770 --> 00:42:23,370
Rym: They're not different.

800
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:28,510
Scott: They just look different so that you can tell that that person is on their second or third continue.

801
00:42:28,930 --> 00:42:31,763
Scott: They don't actually fire faster or do anything like that.

802
00:42:31,783 --> 00:42:33,410
Scott: They definitely don't do more damage.

803
00:42:33,630 --> 00:42:37,450
Rym: However, I have fostered that false belief in other people in order to make them lose.

804
00:42:39,411 --> 00:42:42,808
Scott: How would that make someone lose if they think their cannons are powered up?

805
00:42:43,150 --> 00:42:47,425
Rym: In Katsu-Kan, when we had all those Rampart games we were playing with everybody, I could have lost this game.

806
00:42:48,870 --> 00:42:49,933
Rym: It was kind of dicey.

807
00:42:50,233 --> 00:42:57,429
Rym: I convinced the guy next to me that he should attack the guy one next to him because that guy had the "better cannons".

808
00:42:59,140 --> 00:42:59,610
Scott: Oh, interesting.

809
00:42:59,910 --> 00:43:01,073
Rym: It worked really well.

810
00:43:01,735 --> 00:43:07,050
Rym: Man, that Katsu-Kan, they got a Rampart goddamn machine and they put it in our video game room.

811
00:43:07,430 --> 00:43:10,180
Rym: We ran a Rampart tournament that was surprisingly well attended.

812
00:43:10,561 --> 00:43:12,910
Rym: Rampart is well known and well loved among good gamers.

813
00:43:14,632 --> 00:43:15,235
Rym: So, I don't know.

814
00:43:15,516 --> 00:43:16,200
Rym: Play Rampart.

815
00:43:16,522 --> 00:43:18,049
Rym: If you've never played it, play it.

816
00:43:20,111 --> 00:43:22,061
Rym: There's almost nothing bad to say about this game.

817
00:43:22,382 --> 00:43:23,990
Scott: The only complaints I have are that it's old.

818
00:43:24,471 --> 00:43:28,049
Scott: Yeah, basically it's an old forgotten game and the controls are dated.

819
00:43:28,650 --> 00:43:33,070
Scott: It was designed to work with a trackball and a two-button control system, right?

820
00:43:33,470 --> 00:43:38,950
Scott: But the trackballs on the old arcade machines are difficult to use and very low sensitivity.

821
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:49,490
Scott: And if you try to play any of the Midway Arcade Classics releases or a MAME version, it's going to be really tricky to configure your mouse to work with the game properly.

822
00:43:50,351 --> 00:43:51,212
Scott: It's not going to be good.

823
00:43:52,014 --> 00:44:00,450
Scott: But if someone were to remake the game, the ideal controls would be mouse to move your crosshair when shooting and to click to fire your cannon when shooting.

824
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:08,310
Scott: And when placing Tetris pieces, mouse to move the Tetris piece, scroll wheel to spin the Tetris piece, and mouse click to place the Tetris piece.

825
00:44:08,330 --> 00:44:09,335
Rym: There's one trouble with that.

826
00:44:09,355 --> 00:44:12,330
Rym: We would have to have way bigger maps or somehow make the game more difficult.

827
00:44:12,731 --> 00:44:18,190
Rym: Because I imagine playing right now, if I had a mouse and keyboard, I would literally be all the castles are surrounded.

828
00:44:18,650 --> 00:44:21,479
Scott: Yeah, that's part of the thing.

829
00:44:21,519 --> 00:44:25,070
Scott: Improving the controls would actually make the game too easy.

830
00:44:25,470 --> 00:44:27,324
Rym: Kind of like if you play Halo with a keyboard and mouse.

831
00:44:27,364 --> 00:44:27,707
Rym: that was legit.

832
00:44:28,832 --> 00:44:29,333
Scott: Yeah, right?

833
00:44:29,394 --> 00:44:30,176
Scott: Exactly.

834
00:44:31,840 --> 00:44:35,490
Scott: The thing is you can't not make that control improvement.

835
00:44:35,930 --> 00:44:41,800
Scott: So I think you start by making the control improvement, seeing how the game plays, and then tweaking the game.

836
00:44:41,840 --> 00:44:42,822
Scott: Maybe making it harder.

837
00:44:42,902 --> 00:44:47,870
Scott: Maybe increasing the size or the resolution of the wall squares.

838
00:44:48,110 --> 00:44:54,190
Rym: Of course, just making the game bigger would solve that because the maps are way tiny because of the limitations of the day.

839
00:44:55,251 --> 00:44:59,790
Scott: But the thing is the tininess also makes it hard to put all the pieces in because you're so cramped.

840
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:04,250
Scott: And if you made it bigger, it might be too easy to get your pieces in because the crampedness would go away.

841
00:45:04,810 --> 00:45:10,830
Scott: There needs to be a little rebalancing there if indeed the easier controls make the game too easy.

842
00:45:11,150 --> 00:45:17,389
Rym: Grunts would really fix it because grunts are basically just tanks that drive around and if they touch a castle they surround it and destroy it.

843
00:45:18,310 --> 00:45:20,258
Rym: And then you're just down one castle.

844
00:45:20,640 --> 00:45:22,849
Rym: But also you can't place blocks on top of them.

845
00:45:23,594 --> 00:45:25,870
Rym: And they just wedge themselves in your wall and now you're fucked.

846
00:45:26,910 --> 00:45:28,513
Scott: That could actually be something, right?

847
00:45:28,713 --> 00:45:37,890
Scott: You could have a kind of cannon that shoots over to the other side and is a cannonball, but the cannonball is stuck in the ground.

848
00:45:38,030 --> 00:45:41,039
Rym: So not only does it destroy a spot, it prevents you from building on that spot.

849
00:45:45,030 --> 00:45:46,436
Rym: In the SNES there are villages.

850
00:45:46,516 --> 00:45:50,070
Rym: If you surround a village, it turns into tanks that go attack the other guy.

851
00:45:50,632 --> 00:45:56,310
Rym: If you build over a village or blow a village up on your own side, it turns into tanks that fuck you.

852
00:45:58,210 --> 00:46:02,930
Scott: There's all kinds of creative ways this game can be improved and modified and tricked out.

853
00:46:03,772 --> 00:46:07,910
Scott: And the fact that the base game is just so strong, it's like you can't fuck it up.

854
00:46:08,310 --> 00:46:12,150
Rym: Yeah, James Rolfe keeps saying, well he said it once, we should remake Demons to Diamonds.

855
00:46:13,051 --> 00:46:15,264
Rym: Yeah, it's a good game, but remake Rampart.

856
00:46:15,385 --> 00:46:16,190
Rym: Rampart's way better.

857
00:46:16,250 --> 00:46:17,470
Rym: Not that much harder to remake.

858
00:46:17,892 --> 00:46:20,402
Scott: Yeah, no, not at all.

859
00:46:20,663 --> 00:46:22,350
Scott: Just surround your castles and stay alive.

